    "local_fix": "Move the print before the free (or defer free until after use), e.g., call printLine(data) and then free(data) and set data = NULL. This prevents reading the buffer after it has been freed.",
    "global_fix": "Introduce explicit ownership/lifetime management (e.g., an OwnedString wrapper or RAII types like std::string/unique_ptr) so destruction happens at scope end and consumers only get valid views. This makes the object lifetime explicit and prevents premature frees leading to UAF."
